@page "/about"

<PageTitle>About | Aetheric Forge</PageTitle>

<h1>About the Forge</h1>

<section>
    <h2>Why the Forge Exists</h2>

    <p>
        The software industry excels at creating technology, but often struggles
        to preserve knowledge.
    </p>

    <p>
        The Aetheric Forge Initiative exists to bridge the gap between theory and
        practice by producing software, infrastructure, documentation, and
        educational resources that remain useful long after the latest trend has passed.
    </p>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>Our Mission</h2>

    <p>
        To create open, accessible engineering knowledge and provide practical
        opportunities for individuals to learn by building real systems.
    </p>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>Our Principles</h2>

    <div class="card-grid">
        <article class="card">
            <h3>Build Real Things</h3>
            <p>Experience is created through practice.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="card">
            <h3>Share Knowledge</h3>
            <p>Knowledge grows when it is documented and shared.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="card">
            <h3>Design for Longevity</h3>
            <p>Technology changes quickly. Principles endure.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="card">
            <h3>Learn Continuously</h3>
            <p>Engineering is a lifelong discipline.</p>
        </article>
    </div>
</section>